    <td width="700" background="/lotr/gfx/cloud/bluecc.gif" height="15" valign="bottom"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr><td><font face="Tolk, Times, serif" class="h1font"><font color="#8989B1">Advanced Decks</font></B></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width="2"></td><td valign="top"> 
      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5"><tr><td><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font face="Tolk, Times, serif" class="h1font">Galadriel and her friends/Sauron Hate</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=20185">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=6263">Trevor "JangoFett" Bradley</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> This deck sets up and then abuses Galadriel&#39;s Mirror.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> December 23, 2001</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> Starting <br>
Frodo Son of Drogo<br>
The One Ring Isildur&#39;s Bane<br>
Arwen Daughter of Elrond<br>
Legolas Greenleaf<br>
<br>
Adventure Deck<br>
1) <a href="javascript:card_browser(205)">The Prancing Pony</a><br>
2) <a href="javascript:card_browser(214)">Trollshaw Forest</a><br>
3) <a href="javascript:card_browser(221)">Rivendell Waterfall</a><br>
4) <a href="javascript:card_browser(226)">Moria Stairway</a><br>
5) <a href="javascript:card_browser(228)">The Bridge of Khazad-dum</a><br>
6) Lothlorien Woods<br>
7) <a href="javascript:card_browser(234)">Silverlode Banks</a><br>
8) <a href="javascript:card_browser(238)">Shores of Nen Hithoel</a><br>
9) <a href="javascript:card_browser(243)">Tol Brandir</a><br>
<br>
Free Peoples<br>
Aragorn King in Exile x2<br>
Boromir Lord of Gondor x2<br>
Galadriel Lady of Light x2 <br>
Elrond x2<br>
Celeborn<br>
Rumil <br>
Orophin<br>
Thrarin<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(258)">The Last Alliance of Elves and</a> Men x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(1)">The Choice of Luthien</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(301)">Aragorn&#39;s Bow</a> x2<br>
Gwemgil<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(11)">Ranger&#39;s Sword</a> <br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(305)">Blade of Gondor</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(12)">A Ranger&#39;s Versatility</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(264)">The Mirror of Galadriel</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(247)">Defiance</a> x4<br>
<br>
Shadow<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(147)">Morgul Warden</a> x2<br>
Orc Ambusher x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(154)">Orc Inquisitor</a> x4<br>
Orc Scouting Band x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(133)">Band of the Eye</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(140)">Hate</a> x4<br>
Orc Bowman x4<br>
Under the Watching Eye x4<br>
<br>
  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> This deck tries to setup Galadriel and her mirror and abuses her other abilities with Celeborn, Elrond and the archer brothers Rumil and Orophin. It starts the usual suspects Legolas and Arwen then pulls aragorn. It has all the ranger tricks like last alliance and ranger&#39;s versatility. When you get aragorna and boromir with thier swords and last alliance they make an almost unbeatable pair. Tech cards in the fellowship deck are choice of luthien which helps aragorn use his bow every turn and Thrarin who takes one for the home team. Thrarin is so stout. <br>
<br>
Okay Defiance is not the best card to use with all the rangers Swordsman of the North Kingdom is much better. However, in my area Ringwraiths are very popular and the archer brothers help take care of any other deck type. <br>
<br>
The shadow side is very ruthless. In the early game you just set up the beatdown by getting out Orc Bowman and Under the Watchful Eye. The orc ambusher isnt that good but you need him to get out UtWE, and he is really good at site nine (Tol Brandir) it allows you to swarm pretty well at site nine. <br>
<br>
After site three you start bounding out the orcs. Orc Inquisitor is really good and he compliments the discard element in the fellowship. Band of the eye is such a beating, and his toughness three lets you play multiple Hates. This deck combos very well the conditions make Hate just backbreaking.<br>
<br>
Thanks for reading <br>
JangoFett<br>
<br>
P.S. This deck has won two straight tournaments for me. So it obviousy runs pretty well. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=20185"> Read Reviews </A> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table> <!-- #EndEditable --></td>
